1) Find your network range

Check your IP and subnet mask. If your IP is 192.168.1.34 with mask 255.255.255.0, use 192.168.1.0/24.

2) Run the scanner

Linux/macOS: sudo python3 src/network_scanner.py -t 192.168.1.0/24

3) Optional flags: --iface wlan0        # choose interface
--timeout 4          # wait longer for responses
--json               # output in JSON format
